---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AnniversaryCalculator from '../components/AnniversaryCalculator.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Anniversary Calculator — How Long Have You Been Together? | Clockr"
	description="Calculate how long you've been together, married, or celebrating. See years, months, days elapsed, total days, and countdown to your next anniversary."
	category="birthdays"
>
	<div class="anc-page">
		<div class="anc-header">
			<div class="anc-eyebrow">
				<span class="anc-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				AGE & BIRTHDAYS
			</div>
			<h1 class="anc-title">
				<span class="anc-gradient">Anniversary</span><br />
				<span class="anc-gradient">Calculator</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="anc-subtitle">
				Find out how long you've been together, married, or celebrating
			</p>
		</div>

		<AnniversaryCalculator client:load />

		<section class="anc-how">
			<h2 class="anc-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="anc-how-card">
				<p>
					Clockr calculates the time between your anniversary date and today by
					working through the calendar year by year, month by month, and day by
					day. Rather than assuming every month has 30 days, the tool accounts
					for months of different lengths — from 28 or 29 days in February to
					31 days in January — and includes leap years, where an extra day is
					added every four years. The result is a precise breakdown of years,
					months, and days, plus a total day count.
				</p>
				<p>
					Certain anniversary years carry special meaning in the traditional
					wedding gift list. Paper marks the 1st anniversary, wood the 5th, tin
					or aluminium the 10th, silver the 25th, and gold the 50th. These
					milestones — 1, 5, 10, 25, and 50 years — are widely celebrated
					because they mark meaningful chapters in a relationship. Clockr
					highlights when your next anniversary falls on one of these notable
					years.
				</p>
				<p>
					The next anniversary countdown finds the upcoming occurrence of your
					anniversary date on the calendar. If that date has already passed this
					year, the tool looks ahead to the same day next year — including
					handling 29 February anniversaries in non-leap years. The number of
					days shown is the count from today to that next anniversary date.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="anc-faq">
			<h2 class="anc-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="anc-faq-list">
				<details class="anc-faq-item">
					<summary class="anc-faq-question"
						>How do I calculate how long we've been together?</summary
					>
					<div class="anc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Enter the date your relationship began, your wedding day, or any
							other anniversary you want to track in the date field above. Clockr
							instantly shows how many years, months, and days have passed since
							that date, along with the total number of days. You can also add an
							optional label — such as "Wedding" or "First date" — to personalise
							the result.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="anc-faq-item">
					<summary class="anc-faq-question"
						>What is the traditional gift for each wedding anniversary year?</summary
					>
					<div class="anc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							The traditional wedding anniversary gift list assigns a material to
							each year. Common milestones include paper (1st), cotton (2nd),
							leather (3rd), wood (5th), tin or aluminium (10th), crystal (15th),
							china (20th), silver (25th), pearl (30th), ruby (40th), gold (50th),
							and diamond (60th). Modern lists sometimes suggest different gifts,
							but the traditional themes remain popular for cards, parties, and
							keepsakes.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="anc-faq-item">
					<summary class="anc-faq-question"
						>How many days have we been married?</summary
					>
					<div class="anc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Enter your wedding date and Clockr displays the total number of days
							since that date beneath the years, months, and days breakdown. The
							count includes every calendar day from your wedding day to today,
							accounting for leap years and months of varying length.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="anc-faq-item">
					<summary class="anc-faq-question">When is our next anniversary?</summary>
					<div class="anc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Once you enter your anniversary date, the results show how many days
							until your next anniversary and the exact date it falls on. If your
							anniversary has already passed this calendar year, the tool counts
							down to the same date next year. For future dates, it shows the
							countdown until that first anniversary arrives.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="anc-faq-item">
					<summary class="anc-faq-question"
						>What is considered a milestone anniversary?</summary
					>
					<div class="anc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Milestone anniversaries are typically the 1st, 5th, 10th, 25th, and
							50th years, though many couples also celebrate the 15th, 20th, and
							other round numbers. These years are associated with traditional gift
							themes — paper, wood, tin, silver, and gold — and are often marked
							with parties, trips, or special gifts. Clockr highlights when your
							upcoming anniversary is one of these notable years.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="anc-faq-item">
					<summary class="anc-faq-question"
						>Can I use this for any type of anniversary, not just weddings?</summary
					>
					<div class="anc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Yes. Enter any meaningful date — a first date, engagement, civil
							partnership, work anniversary, or friendship milestone — and use the
							optional label field to describe what you are celebrating. The
							calculator works the same way regardless of the occasion.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="anc-related">
			<h3 class="anc-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="anc-related-grid">
				<a href="/age-calculator" class="anc-related-card"
					><span class="anc-related-name">Age Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/days-until-birthday" class="anc-related-card"
					><span class="anc-related-name">Days Until Birthday</span></a
				>
				<a href="/pregnancy-due-date-calculator" class="anc-related-card"
					><span class="anc-related-name">Pregnancy Due Date Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/life-in-numbers" class="anc-related-card"
					><span class="anc-related-name">Your Life in Numbers</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.anc-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.anc-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.anc-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 10px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.anc-eyebrow-square {
		width: 10px;
		height: 10px;
		border-radius: 3px;
		background: #8b5cf6;
		box-shadow: 0 0 18px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.35);
	}

	.anc-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.anc-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.anc-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0;
	}

	:global(.anc-tool) {
		margin-bottom: 56px;
	}

	:global(.anc-card) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	:global(.anc-inputs) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 18px;
	}

	:global(.anc-input-wrap) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 10px;
		align-items: stretch;
	}

	:global(.anc-label) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	:global(.anc-input) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 16px 24px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 24px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #ffffff;
		text-align: center;
		outline: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
		width: 100%;
		box-sizing: border-box;
	}

	:global(.anc-input--text) {
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	:global(.anc-input::placeholder) {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.25);
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	:global(.anc-input:focus) {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.8);
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
	}

	:global(.anc-presets) {
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	:global(.anc-presets-title) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0 0 12px;
	}

	:global(.anc-presets-grid) {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 10px;
	}

	:global(.anc-preset) {
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.22);
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 14px 12px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75);
		cursor: pointer;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
	}

	:global(.anc-preset:hover) {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.45);
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.08);
	}

	:global(.anc-results) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 32px 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 50px rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.06);
		text-align: center;
	}

	:global(.anc-main) {
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	:global(.anc-main-heading) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 36px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -1.5px;
		line-height: 1.15;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin: 0 0 12px;
	}

	:global(.anc-total-days) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 18px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		margin: 0;
	}

	:global(.anc-next) {
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.18);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 20px 18px;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	:global(.anc-next-line) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0 0 6px;
	}

	:global(.anc-next-line strong) {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	:global(.anc-next-date) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 800;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
		margin: 0;
	}

	:global(.anc-milestone) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0;
		background: rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.06);
		border: 1px solid rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.18);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 12px 14px;
	}

	.anc-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.anc-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.anc-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.anc-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.anc-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.anc-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.anc-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.anc-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.anc-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.anc-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.anc-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.anc-faq-item[open] .anc-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.anc-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.anc-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.anc-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.anc-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.anc-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.anc-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.anc-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.4);
	}

	.anc-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.anc-title {
			font-size: 44px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		:global(.anc-main-heading) {
			font-size: 28px;
		}

		:global(.anc-presets-grid) {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.anc-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
